## What this is

{{ app_title }} â€” generated from the [cloudflare-better-auth-d1 copier template](https://copier.readthedocs.io/). Adapts the [Hono + Better Auth](https://hono.dev/examples/better-auth-on-cloudflare) recipe to use **Cloudflare D1** instead of Neon. One Cloudflare Worker serves both the Better Auth API and a Vite React SPA.

## Layout

```
.                  # Hono Worker (Better Auth on D1)
  src/index.ts              Hono app, mounts /api/auth/* on the better-auth handler
  src/lib/better-auth/      auth() factory â€” drizzleAdapter(drizzle(env.DB), 'sqlite')
  src/db/schema.ts          GENERATED by @better-auth/cli â€” do not edit by hand
  drizzle/                  SQL migrations generated by drizzle-kit from schema.ts
  wrangler.jsonc            D1 binding `DB`, assets binding `ASSETS` â†’ ./web/dist
  better-auth.config.ts     Schema-generation config (uses better-sqlite3 :memory:)
  drizzle.config.ts         dialect: sqlite, driver: d1-http

web/               # Vite React SPA (shadcn preset buFznsW, radix-lyra, phosphor icons)
  src/App.tsx               Auth-gated root (loading â†’ dashboard or login card)
  src/components/login-card.tsx, dashboard.tsx
  src/lib/auth-client.ts    Thin fetch wrapper hitting /api/auth/*
```

Worker serves the SPA through the `assets` binding with `not_found_handling: single-page-application`. `run_worker_first: ["/api/*"]` gates the Worker in front of the assets handler for API routes.

## First-run checklist

1. `bun install` at root and in `web/`
2. `cd web && bun run build` â€” the Worker serves `web/dist`, so this must run before `wrangler dev`
3. `wrangler d1 create {{ d1_database_name }}` â€” paste the returned `database_id` into `wrangler.jsonc`
4. `bun run db:migrate:local` to seed the local D1 with the generated migration
5. Create `.dev.vars` with `BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=$(openssl rand -base64 32)` and `BETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:8787`
6. `bun run dev` â†’ `http://localhost:8787`

## Schema & migration flow

The schema is **generated, not hand-written**. When adding a better-auth plugin or changing `src/lib/better-auth/options.ts`:

```bash
bun run auth:generate      # regenerates src/db/schema.ts from better-auth.config.ts
bun run db:generate        # drizzle-kit turns schema.ts into drizzle/NNNN_*.sql
bun run db:migrate:local   # wrangler d1 migrations apply --local
bun run db:migrate:remote  # wrangler d1 migrations apply --remote
```

`better-auth.config.ts` uses an in-memory `better-sqlite3` DB because the CLI doesn't need a real connection to emit drizzle table definitions â€” only the adapter shape.

## Deploy

```bash
# one-time
wrangler d1 migrations apply {{ d1_database_name }} --remote
wrangler secret put BETTER_AUTH_SECRET   # paste `openssl rand -base64 32`

# every deploy
cd web && bun run build && cd ..
wrangler deploy
```

After the first deploy, update `vars.BETTER_AUTH_URL` in `wrangler.jsonc` to the `*.workers.dev` URL (or custom domain) and redeploy â€” better-auth uses it to issue redirects and cookies.

## Commands

Root (Worker):
```bash
bun run dev                   # wrangler dev â€” local Worker + local D1 + SPA dist
bun run typecheck             # tsc --noEmit against worker-configuration.d.ts
bun run cf-typegen            # wrangler types (regenerate after wrangler.jsonc edits)
bun run deploy                # wrangler deploy
```

Web:
```bash
cd web && bun run dev         # vite dev server on :5173 (proxy API to :8787 if needed)
cd web && bun run build       # MUST run before wrangler dev/deploy â€” Worker serves web/dist
cd web && bun run typecheck
```

The Worker serves `web/dist`, so edits to the SPA are not visible until `bun run build` in `web/`. For live SPA iteration, run `vite dev` directly and point it at `http://localhost:8787/api/*` via a proxy.

## Auth-specific gotchas

- Better Auth requires `env.BETTER_AUTH_SECRET` (a wrangler secret) and `env.BETTER_AUTH_URL`. The Env type is augmented in `src/env.d.ts` to include `BETTER_AUTH_SECRET` since it's not in `wrangler.jsonc`.
- `options.ts` sets `advanced.ipAddress.ipAddressHeaders: ["cf-connecting-ip"]` â€” without this better-auth logs rate-limiter warnings on Workers.
- `auth-client.ts` POSTs `body: "{}"` on sign-out because better-auth parses the body as JSON and crashes on an empty stream.
- The auth handler expects `basePath: "/api/auth"` matching the Hono route mount.
